concept_explanation.fallback_controller:
**Fallback controller for gateway:**

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/fallback")
public class GatewayFallbackController {

    @GetMapping("/payments")
    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> paymentFallback(
            ServerHttpRequest request) {
        return ResponseEntity
            .status(HttpStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE)
            .body(Map.of(
                "error",  "Payment service temporarily unavailable",
                "status", "DEGRADED",
                "retry",  "true"
            ));
    }

    @GetMapping("/catalog")
    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, Object>> catalogFallback() {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(Map.of(
            "products", List.of(),
            "message",  "Product catalog temporarily unavailable",
            "cached",   "false"
        ));
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.key_resolver:
**Rate limit key resolver (per API key):**

```java
@Configuration
public class GatewayConfig {

    // Rate limit by API key header:
    @Bean("apiKeyResolver")
    public KeyResolver apiKeyResolver() {
        return exchange -> {
            String apiKey = exchange.getRequest()
                .getHeaders().getFirst("X-API-Key");
            return Mono.just(
                apiKey != null ? apiKey : exchange.getRequest().getRemoteAddress().toString()
            );
        };
    }

    // Rate limit by user ID:
    @Bean("userIdResolver")
    public KeyResolver userIdResolver() {
        return exchange -> Mono.just(
            exchange.getRequest().getHeaders()
                .getOrDefault("X-User-Id", List.of("anonymous")).get(0)
        );
    }
}
```

